I made this for Thanksgiving, and my relatives thought that I was a culinary prodigy. It was delicious, and so easy to make! I didn't have a tart pan (although after making this, my mom decided I needed one), so I used a springform pan, which worked just fine. I made the cut out chocolate stars from another cake in this Bon Appetit, and I stuck them to the sides of the cake and put them on top. Everyone was very impressed with this simple, fun detail. In the future, I might alter this recipe to become a specialty dessert for the restaurant where I work. Marvelous!

